%N A396937 A knight starts at the origin on an infinite chessboard. In each step, it makes a knight's move to the unvisited point closest to the origin, avoiding steps that inevitably lead to a dead end at some point in the future. a(n) is the y-coordinate of the knight after the n-th step.
%C A396937 See A396936 for details.
